news.title: Gurugram: Three illegal colonies razed, 12 acres freed in Bhondsi & Naya Gaon
news.para: Around 100 structures, including 15 under construction houses, shops and boundary walls were demolished, an official said. in the presence of police during the drive.

news.title: CBI to probe Chintels Paradiso tower collapse
news.para: It was in the middle of May that the Haryana government officially handed over the probe to the CBI after working out all the modalities and the paperwork.

news.title: Ghaziabad police confiscates Rs 5 crore property of a builder under Gangster Act
news.para: ​Dhanpal, the owner of Nidhi builder, used to make builder flats and sell one flat to multiple buyers. Over 15 fraud cases have been lodged against him in different police stations in the district.

news.title: Bombay HC declares Ahuja Properties & Associates with over Rs 10 crore dues insolvent
news.para: The HC single judge bench of Justice Girish Kulkarni passed the order on June 24, in a bunch of 11 insolvency petitions filed in 2019 and 2020, against Ahuja and the partnership firm.

news.title: Mumbai: Mhada to get windfall from Rs 2,000 crore Bandra redevelopment deal
news.para: On Wednesday, Ten X Realty, a subsidiary of Gautam Singhania’s Raymond, and Khar-based CRD Realtors registered a joint development agreement for a 9.5lakh-sqft project that was brokered by property consultants L Lachhmandas & Co.

news.title: Greater Noida: Supercity Developers office sealed for not paying Rs 6.7 crore dues
news.para: Dadri’s sub-divisional magistrate Alok Kumar Gupta said that several homebuyers in the project had moved the UP-Real Estate Regulatory Authority (UP-Rera) seeking refunds from the developer for the delay in possession of their flats.

news.title: Lack of CEO at NLMC delays Rs 28,000 crore land monetisation
news.para: Officials aware of the matter told ET that many CPSEs and ministries have shared a list to offer their surplus lands for monetisation, including land owned by Hindustan Cables Ltd, MTNL, BSNL, Cement Corporation of India (CCI) and the defence ministry. It is waiting for approval from the authorities.

news.title: Ascendas in talks with L&T Realty to buy planned office assets
news.para: The portfolio includes total commercial real estate development potential of over 5 million sq ft across Bengaluru, Chennai and Mumbai.

news.title: Renu Sud, Balasubramanyam Sriram resign as non-executive nominee directors from Unitech board
news.para: While Karnad, who is the MD of HDFC Ltd, resigned from Unitech board on March 24, Balasubramanyam Sriram stepped down on June 13, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: West Bengal: Discount balm for realty sector hikes
news.para: Kolkata has witnessed a slowdown in sales in January-June 2022 when the Reserve Bank announced twin Repo Rate hikes and banks passed them on to consumers by increasing the interest on home loans.

news.title: Realty firm Hines plans to increase its presence in south India
news.para: The company plans to invest a minimum $50 million for each major investment across markets. It will explore new office projects through development management and forward purchase agreements, apart from looking at greenfield acquisitions in prime locations including Mumbai and Gurgaon.

news.title: Delhi government to provide skill training to construction workers
news.para: Under the programme, Delhi Skill and Entrepreneurship University (DSEU) and Delhi Building and Other Construction Workers’ Welfare Board will give training to construction workers at construction sites.

news.title: Ajmera Realty & Infra sales bookings jump over three-fold to Rs 400 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: The carpet area sold by the company stood at 1,57,438 square feet in April-June period of this fiscal as against 61,663 square feet in the year-ago period.

news.title: BuildNext raises $3.5 million in funding round led by Madhumala Ventures
news.para: The company has also secured funding from existing investors Konglo Ventures, Vineet Kumar (CEO, Native) and Deep Gupta (FatEngine) among others.

news.title: HC refuses to quash criminal proceedings against Embassy Group's chairman
news.para: The original complaint was filed against OMR Investments LLP and six of its partners and signatory authorities, including Virwani. Pardhanani Chatrabhuj Bassarmal and Sahadeva Reddy are the complainants.
